Array:-
------
->Arrays are a collection of elements of any type stored in contiguous manner.
->size if fixed i.e., we cannot change once is created.
->every element can be accessed by using index and the index starts from 0 to n-1.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Declaration:-
1.dataType arrayName[]
2.dataType[] arrayName
----------------------------------------------
Initialization:-
->It gives memory to array elements.
ways:
    arrayName=new dataType[size]
   dataType[] arrayName={values}
-------------------------------------------------

->Arrays are mutable i.e., can be changed.
Ex:-
arr[0]=7;//adding
arr[0]=9;//modifying

->we generally see the ArrayOutOfBoundsException in arrays, because of accessing or using the index,
    which is greater than the size of an array.
->

